    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Answer above is almost perfect, but note that it will change variables like <code>_something</code> or <code>this._something</code> into <code>Something</code> and <code>this.Something</code>. I didn't want that in my case, as leading _ was used to denote \"private\" variables (old JS project). I slightly modified this approach:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Find:</strong> (\\w)[_]{1,1}([a-z])</p>\n\n<p><strong>Replace:</strong> $1\\U$2</p>\n\n<p>This will ensure that only variables with <code>_</code> is in the middle will be affected.</p>\n"
  }, {
